snippet.textDisplay: I love the whole progression of expressions that Arin seemingly flirts with when he realizes what Dan has proposed at 3:19, all the way through to when the shot ends at 3:35… Dan’s expressions ALSO but I would really love to know what thoughts were in Arin’s internal stream of consciousness up until Dan takes a bite. I just HAD to stop each frame and view their expressions! There may be something wrong with me – It’s just so darn cute to watch! Paused, the Adam and Eve story came to mind, but also in the frame when their noses brush at 3:31, right when Dan sinks into the bite, the picture made me think of a strange human version of “The Division Bell” Pink Floyd album cover (Dan wore a shirt from the tour on a recent episode, I think). I wonder if Arin genuinely wasn’t expecting Dan to do this and was awash with confusion/excitement/slight-terror/pride/shock/amusement/unknowing of what Dan was REALLY going to do. Thanks for always entertaining us, guys ∞ ♥ ♥

snippet.textDisplay:
@3:24
(my face inches away from the TV screen)

"kiss her Dan, kiss her"

The chemistry of miraculin is pretty amazing, but they don't just "make things taste good" they make acidic things taste sweet and that makes for a lot of interesting interactions with food that you might not expect. Milk, for example, is pretty acidic which makes anything with cheese in it a wild trip. Beer too is quite acidic and miraculin can seriously make some beers into straight-up dessert. Check miracle berries out on Amazon, just remember that if you drink something like vinegar, it can seriously muddle your normal digestive process.
